(1) real world experiences and challenges are relevant frameworks for entrepreneurial success, (2) race has not posed as a barrier for entrepreneurial pursuit, and (3) hard work, discipline and a positive mindset are anchors for success. The literature offers inspirational stories and innovative ideas that define a new age of business in the United States. The book is valuable to the Hispanic-Latino community, teachers and students of entrepreneurship, executives and entrepreneurs, government officials and organizations, policy makers, and minority entrepreneurs worldwide.  aTitle from PDF title page (viewed on December 21, 2014).  a44 0aEntrepreneurshipzUnited States. 0aHispanic American businesspeoplezUnited States.1 aSpain, Michelle Ingram.,eauthor. 0aEntrepreneurship and small business management collection.x1946-5661403University of Alberta Accessuhttp://site.ebrary.com/lib/ualbertagep/Doc?id=10997460  hUAINzEBRARYBEP  aInternet AccesswLCc1i6800020-1001lINTERNETmUAINTERNETrYsYtE-RESOURCEu2/9/2015xE-BOOKzEBRARYBEP01bhttp://viaf.org/viaf/316565844